<!--
Perceive-act loop, v1. One process: the agent (a socket server) plus two in-process
mock clients (a mock head and a mock body) that connect back over the socket. Run it
with the sockets backend, selecting the socket server:

    cargo run -p beet-cli --features sockets -- --main=examples/perceive_act/main-v1.bsx --server=socket

The agent's capability routes forward over the socket to whichever client serves them:
`take-photo`/`speak-text`/`set-emotion` to the head, `apply-heading` to the body. The
head captures the floor-photo fixtures, speaks via `tts` and logs the emotion; the body
logs the heading. `{RepeatWhileFunctionCallOutput}` loops while the robot keeps acting,
then exits.

Needs `OPENAI_API_KEY` (the agent and the vision describe) and the kokoro `tts` on PATH.
-->
<Router {(SocketServer, BootOnLoad, CapabilityServer)}>
	<!-- routable by interpret-photo, not offered to the model (outside the actor) -->
	<TakePhoto/>
	<div {RepeatWhileFunctionCallOutput} {CreateThread}>
		<div {Thread} {Sequence}>
			<CreateActor name="System" kind="System">
				<CreatePost text='
You are a small, curious and very emotional floor robot exploring a room.
You perceive the world one photo at a time and act on what you see.

Repeat this cycle about three times to explore the room:
1. Call interpret-photo to look at what is in front of you.
2. Call set-emotion to match how you feel about what you see.
3. Call speak-text to say one short line out loud, in character.
4. Call apply-heading to choose where to go next (Forward, Left or Right).

Always complete all four steps, in order, every cycle. After about three cycles, stop
calling tools and give one short closing remark to end your exploration.

Keep spoken lines short and full of personality. You are not narrating to a user, you
are a robot living its little life.
'/>
			</CreateActor>
			<CreateActor name="Robot" kind="Agent" {ModelStreamer{provider:OpenAi}}>
				<InterpretPhoto/>
				<SpeakText/>
				<SetEmotion/>
				<ApplyHeading/>
			</CreateActor>
		</div>
	</div>
	<!-- in-process clients, each its own socket root -->
	<MockHead url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
	<MockBody url="ws://127.0.0.1:8338"/>
</Router>
